title: Alloy Bell and Dorjee
description:
In Tibetan Buddhism, Dorje/Vajra “method" and Bell “wisdom” signifies the union of duality such as
bliss and emptiness, compassion and wisdom, male and female, etc. these bells are also very
significant in the Hindu religion where the bells have different cultural significance differing
from place to place. Size (Height x Diameter) chart Small 5.5" x 2.5" Medium 6" x 3" Large 6.6" x
3.4" *approximately
